Now *create your own* — it's free, easy, & beautiful

fields.title:
PREFACE 

Our prototype surveys use off-the-shelf software. When we're able to design and engineer them ourselves, surveys will be easier and faster for users to complete. 

Note: you can return to prior answers by using the up or down arrow key on the survey.

Your answers to the following questions will help us design a lifetime of travel experiences for _you_. 

Please think about our questions *from your perspective only*—not from that of your spouse, friends, or family.

Take your time, preferably when you have about 20 minutes in a quiet space.

choices.label: I like staying in my comfort zone—I see travel as a chance to unwind in places that are familiar and not too foreign
I'm willing to venture a bit beyond my comfort zone—I see travel as an opportunity not just to relax, but also to learn and experience new things
I'm open to pushing my comfort zone—I value experiencing new worlds and cultures that are different from my own

fields.title:
People have, at most, 50-60 years to see the world. While this seems like plenty of time, life gets busy. 

Which statements apply to you?  You can choose more than one answer.

choices.label: I see travel primarily as a way to explore as much of the world as I can during my lifetime, within reason.
I see travel primarily as vacation getaways to relax and unwind in mostly one place, then head home
I prefer to travel closer to home, mainly within my own country or continent. Why go elsewhere when there’s plenty to see nearby?
Europe is my favorite continent. There’s so much to see there that I’m not really motivated to explore other continents.
I see travel primarily as something I’ll do when I retire

*I'm more of a city person*—I like the hustle and bustle, the energy, sights, and museums. I'm all about the melting pot of people, cultures, food, nightlife and beyond. Big cities like New York, Paris, and Tokyo excite me.
*I'm more of a nature person*—I like the peace and quiet of natural environments, such as the beach, mountains, or countryside. I like adventure/exploring what nature has to offer.
*I like both*—I like a mix of cities and natural environments
